// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception
//
// test/parse/notes/n10/fail.test — N10 (lang.ebnf:1075) locked-text
// assertion for the `label`-as-identifier warning.
//
// CAVEAT — naming.  N10 produces a WARNING, not an error: the
// identifier is still accepted (FR-017) and the parser exits
// successfully. The conventional `fail.test` filename is therefore
// misleading here; we keep it to satisfy tasks.md T039's
// `{pass-warning.test, fail.test}` enumeration and to give FR-027's
// "failing-shape" diagnostic-text assertion a stable home.
//
// This fixture's sole job is to pin the diagnostic STRING per
// FR-027 — it deliberately overlaps with `pass-warning.test`'s
// CHECK on the warning text, but is structured to give a clean
// failure if Track D's diagnostic constant ever drifts (a CodeRabbit
// reviewer can grep `'label' is reserved; using as identifier` and
// see the lock).
//
// Why this is not a hard error: per `lang.ebnf §15` line 783-824,
// `label` is reserved but unused in real code; the spec's note (N10
// at lang.ebnf:1075-1081) explicitly chooses the warn-and-accept
// semantics for forward compatibility. Promoting to an error
// would require a spec amendment per Principle VII.
//
// FR-029 RED state: at 7bc1aea, no `-emit=ast` flag; RUN exits 2;
// CHECK fails. Principle VIII.

// RUN: %nslc -emit=ast %s 2>&1 | FileCheck %s

module n10_label_fail {
    wire label;
}

// FR-027 locked-string assertion.
// CHECK: warning: 'label' is reserved; using as identifier (parser-note N10)
